<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
    
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, shrink-to-fit=no">
    <title>Request+ - Spotify Overlay!</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.12.0/css/all.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main/style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-light navbar-expand">
        <div class="container"><a class="navbar-brand" href="/">Request+ - Spotify Overlay!</a></div>
        <div class="d-block text-center"><a class="btn btn-success btn-lg nav-btn" href="/logout" role="button">Logout</a></div>
    </nav>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card bg-light mt-4">
            <!-- Make a selection menu to select what style of overlay you want -->
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Settings > Channel Points</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Below are a few options to manage the Song Request Channel Point. Please choose from the following options.</p>

                <p class="card-text">Please edit the price at twitch's management page located <a href="https://dashboard.twitch.tv/u/<%=user.data[0].login%>/viewer-rewards/channel-points/rewards">here</a>. (YOU ALSO NEED TO ENABLE IT THERE TOO)</p>
                <br>
                <div class="btn-container">
                    <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg nav-btn" onclick="createChannelPoints()" role="button">Create Channel Point</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg nav-btn" onclick="deleteChannelPoints()" role="button">Delete Channel Point</button>
                </div>
                <p class="card-text">Unfortunately, this is the only options at this time. A full configurator for these will be made in the furture.</p>
                
            <br>
            <!-- make a login with spotify button -->
            
                        
            <div id="user-info" style="display: none;">
            <div id="user"><%=user.data[0].login%></div>
            <div id="user-id"><%=user.data[0].id%></div>
            <div id="user-description"><%=user.data[0].description%></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card bg-light mt-4 mb-4">
            Copyright Â© 2024 Request+<br>
            Request+ is not affiliated with Spotify.
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="/js/main/apichannel.js"></script>


</body>
</html>